RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Blend: AI training + automation + selective VA

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
OTA booking reconciliation, roster management, event enquiry coordination, supplier invoice matching, guest review responses, health & safety audit records, and payroll across multiple sites.

UK AI ADOPTION (use in conversation):
Barclays Business Prosperity Index (Aug 2025): 89% of UK businesses plan AI use within two years; SMEs (10–49 staff) averaged £125k AI investment vs £400k for 250+ employee firms. Lloyds Business Barometer (Mar 2026): 66% have invested in AI, mostly under £25k—39% cite AI/digital skills shortage. Hospitality groups adopted booking tech but AI for roster optimisation, guest comms, and revenue management remains chain-led, not regional SMBs.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA poor for real-time guest complaints needing manager authority—automate booking admin and review responses; VA for event enquiry overflow only.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Automate OTA reconciliation
• AI guest review response drafts
• Train GMs on AI roster and revenue tips

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• How much time does the team spend on the highest-volume admin tasks in hospitality / hotel groups (regional)?
• Have they piloted AI tools internally, or only client-facing tech?
• Who owns operations/process improvement — and is AI training on anyone''s KPIs?
• What would ''win'' look like in 90 days: hours saved, fewer errors, or staff confident using AI?

